6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. R.S. 22:868(B) is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
8 §868. Limiting actions; jurisdiction; venue
9 * * *
10 B.(1) No insurance contract delivered or issued for delivery in this state and
11 covering subjects located, resident, or to be performed in this state, or any health and
12 accident policy insuring a resident of this state regardless of where made or
13 delivered, shall contain any condition, stipulation, or agreement limiting right of
14 action against the insurer to a period of less than twenty-four months next after the
15 inception of the loss when the claim is a first-party claim, as defined in R.S. 22:1692,
16 and arises under any insurance classified and defined in R.S. 22:47(6), (10), (11),
17 (12), (13), (15), and (19) or to a period of less than one year from the time when the
18 cause of action accrues in connection with all other insurances unless otherwise
19 specifically provided in this Code. An insurer's payment under the terms of a policy
20 of insurance classified and defined in R.S. 22:47(6), (10) through (13), (15), and (19)
21 shall not be considered the acknowledgment of a debt or otherwise serve to extend
22 the contractually defined prescriptive period which begins running at the inception
23 of the loss.
